  • Method Details

    • personIdentification

      boolean personIdentification(String personName) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Create a new person. The personName should not correspond to a person that is already an instance of the class of persons. Creation of a new person should not lead to any inconsistency.
      Parameters:
      personName - fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the person to be created i.e. kl:personName.
      Returns:
      True if the person is successfully created.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the person is already identified, or an inconsistency occurs upon creating a new person.

    • removePerson

      boolean removePerson(String personName) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Delete a person. The personName should correspond to a person that is already an instance of the class of Persons. Removing a person, should also result in the removal of knowledge observations associated with it. Removal of a person should not lead to any inconsistency.
      Parameters:
      personName - fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the person to be created i.e. kl:personName.
      Returns:
      True if the person is removed successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the person is not identified, or an inconsistency occurs upon removing an existing person.

    • knowledgeAssetIdentification

      boolean knowledgeAssetIdentification(String knowledgeAssetName, Set<Feature> featureSet) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Create a new knowledge asset. The knowledgeAssetName should not correspond to a knowledge asset that is already an instance of the class of knowledge assets. The knowledge asset is associated with a set of knowledge asset features which should be defined in OntoKL.
      Parameters:
      knowledgeAssetName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the knowledge asset identified i.e. kl:KnowledgeAssetName.
      featureSet - Set of knowledge asset features associated with a knowledge asset.
      Returns:
      True if the knowledge asset is created successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the knowledge asset is already identified, features/values not defined in OntoKL, or an inconsistency occurs upon creating the knowledge asset.

    • removeKnowledgeAsset

      boolean removeKnowledgeAsset(String knowledgeAssetName) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Removes a knowledge asset. The knowledge asset should correspond to a knowledge asset that is already an instance of the class of knowledge assets. Removing a knowledge asset, should result in the removal of feature value and knowledge observations associated with it.
      Parameters:
      knowledgeAssetName - The name of the knowledge asset to be removed.
      Returns:
      True if the knowledge asset is removed successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the knowledge asset is not identified, or an inconsistency occurs upon removing the knowledge asset.

    • knowledgeObservation

      boolean knowledgeObservation(String personName, String knowledgeAssetName, int n) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Create a knowledge observation. The personName should correspond to a person that is already an instance of the class of persons, the knowledgeAssetName should correspond to an instance of the class of knowledge assets. The integer n represents the extent of which the given person knows the given knowledge asset.
      Parameters:
      personName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the person identified i.e. kl:PersonName.
      knowledgeAssetName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the knowledge asset identified i.e. kl:KnowledgeAssetName.
      n - Value of magnitude.
      Returns:
      True if the knowledge observation is created successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the person or knowledge asset is not identified, or an inconsistency occurs upon creating the knowledge observation.

    • relatedTo

      boolean relatedTo(String knowledgeAsset1Name, String knowledgeAsset2Name) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Establishes a generic relation between two given knowledge assets, knowledgeAsset1 related to knowledgeAsset2, provided that both are instances of kl:KnowledgeAsset.
      Parameters:
      knowledgeAsset1Name - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the subject of relationship, i.e. kl:KnowledgeAsset1Name.
      knowledgeAsset2Name - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the object of relationship, i.e. kl:KnowledgeAsset2Name.
      Returns:
      True if the knowledge asset relationship is established successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If any of the two given knowledge assets is not identified, or an inconsistency occurs upon creating the knowledge asset relationship.

    • dependentOn

      boolean dependentOn(String knowledgeAsset1Name, String knowledgeAsset2Name) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Establishes a dependency between two given knowledge assets, knowledgeAsset1 related to knowledgeAsset2, provided that both are instances of kl:KnowledgeAsset.
      Parameters:
      knowledgeAsset1Name - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the subject of relationship, i.e. kl:KnowledgeAsset1Name.
      knowledgeAsset2Name - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the object of relationship, i.e. kl:KnowledgeAsset2Name.
      Returns:
      True if the knowledge asset relationship is established successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If any of the two given knowledge assets is not identified, or an inconsistency occurs upon creating the knowledge asset relationship.

    • createTeam

      boolean createTeam(String teamName) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Creates a team. The teamName should not be a declared entity,
      Parameters:
      teamName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the team, i.e. kl:teamName
      Returns:
      True if the team is created successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the team is already a subclass of the class of persons, or an inconsistency occurs upon creating the team

    • addPersonToTeam

      boolean addPersonToTeam(String teamName, String personName) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Adds a person to a team. The given person should be an instance of the class of persons. The team should be a subclass of the class of persons.
      Parameters:
      teamName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the team, i.e. kl:teamName
      personName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the person to be added to the team, i.e. kl:personName
      Returns:
      True if the team is created successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the person or team are not identified, or if the person is already a member of the team, or if an inconsistency occurs upon adding the person to the team.

    • deleteTeam

      boolean deleteTeam(String teamName) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Deletes an existing team.
      Parameters:
      teamName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the team, i.e. kl:teamName
      Returns:
      True if the team is deleted successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the team is not identified, or a person is already a member of team, or if an inconsistency occurs upon deleting the team.

    • removePersonFromTeam

      boolean removePersonFromTeam(String teamName, String personName) throws KnowledgeGraphConstructorException
      Removes a person from team.
      Parameters:
      teamName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the team, i.e. kl:teamName
      personName - Fragment identifier of IRI used to represent the person to be removed from team, i.e. kl:personName
      Returns:
      True if the person is removed from team successfully.
      Throws:
      KnowledgeGraphConstructorException - If the person or team is not identified, or if the person is not a member of the team, or if an inconsistency occurs upon deleting the person from the team.
